    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but i've been reading some stuff online saying that originalism is basically just a way for judges to push a specific political agenda under the guise of law. how would a scholar respond to the criticism that originalism is basically just \"lawmaking\" by looking for whatever historical meaning fits their desired outcome?",
